text: Matt Kenseth (born March 10, 1972) is an American race car driver. He drove for Joe Gibbs Racing and Roush Fenway Racing before he retired. In 2003, Kenseth won the NASCAR Winston Cup Championship. ==References== Category:NASCAR drivers Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:American racecar drivers Category:Daytona 500 winners Category:Sportspeople from Wisconsin
